The paper deals with the problem of mining correlated heavy hitters from a data stream, which is a topic related to data structures (cs.DS), databases (cs.DB), and data mining (cs.DM). The algorithm proposed in the paper is based on counters and involves probabilistic techniques, which are also relevant to information theory (cs.IT). The most likely category is cs.DS, followed by cs.DB and cs.DM, while cs.SI and cs.IT are less likely but still possible.
